Title: 1. Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?
description: A middle-aged New England associate professor and his wife, with the help of alcohol, use their young guests to fuel anguish and emotional pain towards each other over the course of a distressing night.

Title: 2. The Good, the Bad and the Ugly
description: A bounty-hunting scam joins two men in an uneasy alliance against a third in a race to find a fortune in gold buried in a remote cemetery.

Title: 3. The Battle of Algiers
description: In the 1950s, fear and violence escalate as the people of Algiers fight for independence from the French government.

Title: 4. Masculine Feminine
description: A romance between young Parisians, shown through a series of vignettes.

Title: 5. Andrei Rublev
description: The life, times and afflictions of the fifteenth-century Russian iconographer St. Andrei Rublev.

Title: 6. Made in U.S.A
description: In the near future, leftist writer Paula goes from Paris to the French town of Atlantic-Cité when she learns of the death of a former colleague and lover, Richard P. Is she there to investigate? On the surface, faces are beautiful, colors bright, clothes trendy. Beneath, little is clear: some talk to Paula as if she's Alice in Wonderland, corpses pile up, and ideological struggles insert themselves. A murder victim's nephew and a political party's hired hands hover around Paula. Is obscuring things her goal or is it life that's obscure?

Title: 7. Au hasard Balthazar
description: The story of a mistreated donkey and the people around him. A study on saintliness and a sister piece to Bresson's Mouchette.

Title: 8. The Nun
description: Suzanne is forced against her will to take vows as a nun and three mothers superior treat her in radically different ways. Suzanne's virtue brings disaster to everyone in this faithful adaptation of a bitter attack on religious abuses.

Title: 9. Django
description: A coffin-dragging gunslinger and a prostitute become embroiled in a bitter feud between a Klan of Southern racists and a band of Mexican Revolutionaries.

Title: 10. King of Hearts
description: During World War I, a British private, sent ahead to a French town to scout for enemy presence, is mistaken for a King by the colorful patients of an insane asylum.

Title: 11. Time to Die
description: After serving his conviction, a former gunman returns to his town planning to live a quiet life, however, the sons of a man he killed have other plans.

Title: 12. Daisies
description: After realizing that all world is spoiled, Marie and Marie are committed to be spoiled themselves. They rip off older men, feast in lavish meals and do all kinds of mischief. But what is all this leading to?

Title: 13. The Endless Summer
description: The crown jewel to ten years of Bruce Brown surfing documentaries. Brown follows two young surfers around the world in search of the perfect wave, and ends up finding quite a few in addition to some colorful local characters.

Title: 14. Fahrenheit 451
description: In an oppressive future, a fireman whose duty is to destroy all books begins to question his task.

Title: 15. The Swinger
description: An authoress writes a steaming sex-novel and proceeds to live out her heroine's adventures.

Title: 16. Blow-Up
description: A fashion photographer unknowingly captures a death on film after following two lovers in a park.

Title: 17. El Dorado
description: Cole Thornton, a gunfighter for hire, joins forces with old friend, Sheriff J.P. Hara. Together with an old Indian fighter and a gambler, they help a rancher and his family fight a rival rancher who's trying to steal their water.

Title: 18. The Trouble with Angels
description: Two high-spirited young students at St. Francis Academy keep things hopping for the challenged Mother Superior and her staff of bewildered Sisters.

Title: 19. Persona
description: A nurse is put in charge of a mute actress and finds that their personae are melding together.

Title: 20. A Man for All Seasons
description: The story of Sir Thomas More, who stood up to King Henry VIII when the King rejected the Roman Catholic Church to obtain a divorce and remarry.

Title: 21. Seconds
description: An unhappy middle-aged banker agrees to a procedure that will fake his death and give him a completely new look and identity - one that comes with its own price.

Title: 22. Nevada Smith
description: A half-American Indian / half-Caucasian young man evolves into a hardened killer as he tracks down the men who murdered his parents.

Title: 23. Harper
description: Cool private investigator Lew Harper is hired by a wealthy California matron to locate her kidnapped husband.

Title: 24. The Sand Pebbles
description: In 1926, a U.S. Naval engineer gets assigned to a gunboat on a rescue mission in war-torn China.

Title: 25. One Million Years B.C.
description: Prehistoric man Tumak is banished from his savage tribe and meets pretty Loana, who belongs to a gentler coastal tribe, but he must fight caveman Payto to win her favors.

Title: 26. Batman: The Movie
description: The Dynamic Duo face four super-villains who plan to hold the world for ransom with the help of a secret invention that instantly dehydrates people.

Title: 27. Funeral in Berlin
description: Sent to East Berlin to retrieve a Communist defector, British spy Harry Palmer suspects the situation is not what his superiors believe it to be.

Title: 28. Fantastic Voyage
description: When a blood clot renders a scientist comatose, a submarine and its crew are shrunk and injected into his bloodstream in order to save him.

Title: 29. Grand Prix
description: American Grand Prix driver Pete Aron is fired by his Jordan-BRM racing team after a crash at Monaco that injures his British teammate, Scott Stoddard.

Title: 30. The Chase
description: The citizens of a small Texas town become worried and panicked when a local bad boy escapes prison and heads for his hometown.

Title: 31. The Fortune Cookie
description: A crooked lawyer persuades his brother-in-law to feign a serious injury in order to collect a big insurance payout.

Title: 32. How to Steal a Million
description: The daughter of an art forger teams up with a burglar to steal one of her father's forgeries and protect his secret.

Title: 33. A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum
description: A wily Roman slave schemes to earn his freedom by romantically uniting his master with a courtesan. But matters get complicated and he ends up dragging in his neighbors around him, leading to chaos.

Title: 34. Alfie
description: Unrepentant ladies' man Alfie Elkins gradually begins to understand the consequences of his lifestyle in 1960s London.

Title: 35. Manos: The Hands of Fate
description: A family gets lost on the road and stumbles upon a hidden, underground, devil-worshiping cult led by the fearsome Master and his servant Torgo.

Title: 36. The Professionals
description: An arrogant Texas millionaire hires four adventurers to rescue his kidnapped wife from a notorious Mexican bandit.

Title: 37. The Russians Are Coming the Russians Are Coming
description: Without hostile intent, a Soviet submarine runs aground off New England. Men are sent for a boat, but many villagers go into a tizzy, risking bloodshed.

Title: 38. Modesty Blaise
description: Stylish ex-con Modesty Blaise and her partner Willie Garvin are tasked by the British Secret Service with preventing her rival Gabriel from stealing diamonds that are to be delivered to her adoptive father, a Sheikh.

Title: 39. The Bible in the Beginning...
description: Extravagant production of the first part of the book of Genesis. Its main highlights are the Garden of Eden, the first brothers, Noah and his family obeying God to build an ark for the Flood and Abraham's attempted sacrifice of Isaac.

Title: 40. Torn Curtain
description: An American scientist publicly defects to East Germany as part of a cloak and dagger mission to steal a formula before planning an escape back to the West.

Title: 41. The Blue Max
description: A young pilot in the German air force of 1918, disliked as lower-class and unchivalrous, tries ambitiously to earn the medal offered for 20 kills.

Title: 42. Hawaii
description: An American missionary and his wife travel to the exotic island kingdom of Hawaii, intent on converting the natives. But the clash between the two cultures is too great and instead of understanding there comes tragedy.

Title: 43. The Silencers
description: Retired secret agent Matt Helm is re-activated in order to stop an evil organization from starting WWIII by exploding an atomic bomb over the USA.

Title: 44. Gambit
description: An English cat burglar needs a Eurasian dancer's help to pull off the perfect heist, but even the most foolproof schemes have a way of backfiring.

Title: 45. The Glass Bottom Boat
description: After a series of misunderstandings, the head of an aerospace research laboratory begins to suspect that his new girlfriend is a Russian spy.

Title: 46. A Man and a Woman
description: A widow and a widower find their relationship developing into love, but their past tragedies prove hard to overcome, causing them to proceed with utmost delicacy.

Title: 47. Carry on Screaming!
description: The sinister Dr Watt has an evil scheme going. He's kidnapping beautiful young women and turning them into mannequins to sell to local stores.

Title: 48. Khartoum
description: In the Sudan, in 1884 to 1885, Egyptian forces led by British General Charles "Chinese" Gordon (Charlton Heston) defend Khartoum against an invading Muslim Army led by a religious fanatic, Mohammed Ahmed el Mahdi (Sir Laurence Olivier).

Title: 49. Don't Look Now... We're Being Shot At!
description: Several ordinary Frenchmen go on an epic voyage through the occupied country to the free zone as they help British pilots avoid German captivity.

Title: 50. Made in Paris
description: An ex model, sales girl and assistant buyer for an NYC dress store lets her hair down when sent to Paris as fashion buyer.

Title: 51. This Property Is Condemned
description: The dramatic love story of small-town Mississippi girl Alva Starr and railroad official Owen Legate, set during the Great Depression.

Title: 52. Our Man Flint
description: When scientists use eco-terrorism to impose their will on the world by affecting extremes in the weather, Intelligence Chief Cramden calls in top agent Derek Flint.

Title: 53. Dracula: Prince of Darkness
description: Ten years after his demise, Count Dracula is resurrected by his servant and preys on four unsuspecting English tourists who have taken shelter in his castle.

Title: 54. The Group
description: Eight inseparable college friends become involved in widely differing lifestyles after graduation.

Title: 55. Murderers' Row
description: Handsome top-secret American agent Matt Helm must recover a laser-weapons inventor who has been kidnapped by arch-villain Julian Wall.

Title: 56. The Rare Breed
description: An English woman and her daughter enlist the aid of a cowboy to try and get their hardy hornless bull to mate with the longhorns of Texas, but have to overcome greedy criminals and the natural elements.

Title: 57. Walk Don't Run
description: During the housing shortage of the Summer Olympic Games in 1964, two men and a woman share a small apartment in Tokyo, and the older man soon starts playing Cupid to the younger pair.

Title: 58. Arabesque
description: International intrigue in London, involving an American university professor, an Arab prime minister, a ruthless businessman, a beautiful spy, and hieroglyphics.

Title: 59. Cast a Giant Shadow
description: In 1947, following the U.N. decision to split British Palestine into separate Jewish and Arab states, a former U.S. Army officer is recruited by the Jews to reorganize the Haganah.

Title: 60. Island of Terror
description: An isolated remote island community is threatened by an attack by tentacled silicates which liquefy and digest bone and tissue.

Title: 61. The Face of Another
description: A businessman with a disfigured face obtains a lifelike mask from his doctor, but the mask starts altering his personality.

Title: 62. The Ghost and Mr. Chicken
description: A timid typesetter hasn't a ghost of a chance of becoming a reporter--until he decides to solve a murder mystery and ends up spending a fright-filled night in a haunted house.

Title: 63. Duel at Diablo
description: In Apache territory, a supply Army column heads for the next fort, an ex-scout searches for the killer of his Indian wife, and a housewife abandons her husband in order to rejoin her Apache lover's tribe.

Title: 64. Closely Watched Trains
description: An apprentice train dispatcher looks for love while aiding his colleagues in their resistance against the Nazis.

Title: 65. Cul-de-sac
description: In search of help, two wounded gangsters on the run find refuge in the secluded castle of a feeble man and his wife; however, under the point of a gun, nothing is what it seems.

Title: 66. Chelsea Girls
description: Lacking a formal narrative, Warhol's art house classic follows various residents of the Chelsea Hotel in 1966 New York City, presented in a split screen with a single audio track in conjunction with one side of screen.

Title: 67. Incident at Phantom Hill
description: After a convoy carrying a million dollars in gold is ambushed, an army captain is sent on a secret mission to retrieve the bullion with the reluctant help of one of the robbers.

Title: 68. Born Free
description: The story of George and Joy Adamson and the orphaned lion cub, Elsa, they adopt.

Title: 69. The Shooting
description: A mysterious woman persuades two cowboys to help her in a revenge scheme.

Title: 70. Ride in the Whirlwind
description: Three cowboys, mistaken for members of an outlaw gang, are relentlessly pursued by a posse.

Title: 71. Mondo Topless
description: Completely topless. Completely uninhibited. The craze that began in San Francisco is now exploding across the USA and Europe.

Title: 72. Is Paris Burning?
description: August 1944. The Allies are approaching Paris and resistance groups within the city start to plan an uprising against the Germans. However, Hitler wants the city destroyed if it looks like the Allies will take it.

Title: 73. Follow Me, Boys!
description: A man settles down in a small town and becomes the scoutmaster.

Title: 74. What Did You Do in the War, Daddy?
description: In World War II, a strategic Italian village agrees to surrender to the Allies only if it's allowed to organize a celebratory festival while giving aerial reconnaissance the false impression of fierce ground fighting.

Title: 75. Paradise, Hawaiian Style
description: Rick Richards is a helicopter pilot who wants to set up a charter flying service in Hawaii -- along the way he makes some friends, including a young Hawaiian girl and her father, romances Judy Hudson, and sings a few songs.

Title: 76. Blood Bath
description: A crazed artist who believes himself to be the reincarnation of a murderous vampire kills young women, then boils their bodies in a vat.

Title: 77. Georgy Girl
description: A young woman juggles an unwanted suitor's advances and her desire for an exciting life, envying her free-spirited roommate's social whirlwind.

Title: 78. Kill, Baby... Kill!
description: A Carpathian village is haunted by the ghost of a murderous little girl, prompting a coroner and a medical student to uncover her secrets while a witch attempts to protect the villagers.

Title: 79. Navajo Joe
description: A Native American warrior seeks revenge on the gang of sadistic scalphunters-turned-bank robbers who massacred his tribe.

Title: 80. The Ugly Dachshund
description: The Garrisons live with a Great Dane who thinks he's a dainty dachshund. His identity crisis results in an uproarious series of household crises that reduce the Garrisons' house to shambles.

Title: 81. Tokyo Drifter
description: After his gang disbands, a yakuza enforcer looks forward to life outside of organized crime but soon must become a drifter after his old rivals attempt to assassinate him.

Title: 82. Eye of the Devil
description: Workers employed at a French vineyard quietly follow old pagan rituals that call for the life of the marquis owner to save his crops during dry seasons.

Title: 83. Munster, Go Home!
description: The Munsters travel to England after Herman discovers he's the new Lord of the Munster Hall.

Title: 84. Queen of Blood
description: In 1990, aliens contact Earth announcing their visit. Their ship crashes on Mars. A rescue team from Earth is dispatched to investigate the alien crash site.

Title: 85. The Appaloosa
description: Man tries to recover a horse stolen from him by a Mexican bandit.

Title: 86. The War Game
description: A docudrama depicting a hypothetical nuclear attack on Britain.

Title: 87. Women of the Prehistoric Planet
description: A spaceship crashes upon an unexplored planet, and the rescuers sent to search for survivors discover that decades have passed due to time dilation.

Title: 88. The Family Way
description: Compassionate look at the troubles of two young newlyweds, whose marriage has yet to be consummated.

Title: 89. Le deuxième souffle
description: A gangster escapes jail and quickly makes plans to continue his criminal ways elsewhere, but a determined inspector is closing in.

Title: 90. Black Girl
description: A black girl from Senegal becomes a servant in France.

Title: 91. Incubus
description: On a strange island inhabited by demons and spirits, a man battles the forces of evil.

Title: 92. Spinout
description: Band singer/race driver Mike McCoy must choose between marrying a beautiful rich girl and driving her father's car in a prestigious race.

Title: 93. Hot Rods to Hell
description: The new owner of a motel in the California desert has a run-in with a gang of delinquent teenage hot rod drivers.

Title: 94. The Sword of Doom
description: Through his unconscionable actions against others, a sociopath samurai builds a trail of vendettas that follow him closely.

Title: 95. Frankie and Johnny
description: A riverboat singer with a weakness for gambling wants to find his lucky redhead, but his girlfriend Frankie is not amused.

Title: 96. Penelope
description: Comedy about a flighty, bored, kleptomaniac wife of a banker who robs her husband's bank of $60,000.

Title: 97. Cyborg 2087
description: Earth's civilization of the future sends a cyborg back to the 1960s to change the future.

Title: 98. The Night of the Grizzly
description: Ex-lawman Jim Cole retires to Wyoming to farm his land, but a land-greedy neighbor, an ex-con turned bounty hunter, and a vicious grizzly bear upset his retirement plans.

Title: 99. The Trap
description: A fur trapper takes a mute girl as his unwilling wife to live with him in his remote cabin in the woods.

Title: 100. Madame X
description: After her lover is killed, the wife of a wealthy man is convinced to fake her own death, which leads her into greater depths of depravity until fate reunites her with her long-lost son, who is unaware of her real identity.

Title: 101. Bang! Bang! You're Dead!
description: One of six travelers who catch the bus from Casablanca airport to Marrakesh is carrying $2 million to pay a local operator to fix United Nations votes. But which one?

Title: 102. The War of the Gargantuas
description: A giant, cannibalistic humanoid's rampage through Tokyo is halted by his more docile twin, but neither their reunion nor their scientist caretakers can prevent their eventual duel.

Title: 103. Return of the Seven
description: Two survivors of the original Magnificent Seven, Chris and Vin, recruit four new members to re-form the outfit and defend several Mexican villages from vicious bandits.

Title: 104. You're a Big Boy Now
description: Confused post-teenage virgin Bernard Chanticleer moves to New York City, falls for cold-hearted inscrutable go-go dancer Barbara Darling, then finds true love with a loyal lass.

Title: 105. Night Games
description: The story about a man who's trying to get rid of his memories from his past. He grew up in an upper-class family in a castle and now revisits the castle with his fiancee.

Title: 106. A Fine Madness
description: Samson Shillitoe, mad genius of a poet irresistible to women, but plagued by writer's block, agrees to see a psychiatrist, and his beautiful wife.

Title: 107. A Big Hand for the Little Lady
description: Comedy western in which a traveler bets more money than he can afford in a poker game, and unusual events follow.

Title: 108. The Fear
description: A disturbing family drama about the pathogeny of Greek countryside.

Title: 109. Rasputin: The Mad Monk
description: Thrown out of his monastery for licentious and drunken behavior, Rasputin travels to St Petersburg in pursuit of wealth and prestige. He soon gains influence at court with his powers of healing and of hypnotism.

Title: 110. The Witch
description: A womanizing author is lured to a mansion by an old woman under the guise of working as a librarian. Her daughter, Aura, appears out of nowhere and begins to seduce him. Little does he know, Aura doesn't actually exist.

Title: 111. Dimension 5
description: An American intelligence agent aided by a Chinese-American female agent uses a time-travel belt to thwart Chinese operatives who are attempting to import to Los Angeles the materials to make an atomic bomb.

Title: 112. Dead Heat on a Merry-Go-Round
description: A paroled conman co-ordinates the robbery of an L. A. Airport bank with the arrival of the Soviet premier.

Title: 113. The Hawks and the Sparrows
description: Totò and his son Ninetto are drifting on a road in Italy when they meet a speaking crow.

Title: 114. The Wild Angels
description: The "Angels", a San Pedro motorcycle gang, party their way through the Coachella Valley while searching for a bike stolen from them by Mexicans, clashing with police along the way.

Title: 115. Stagecoach
description: On the stagecoach to Cheyenne, a mixed group of passengers must work together to survive the arduous journey and the Indian attacks.

Title: 116. Ride Beyond Vengeance
description: After an 11-year absence, a buffalo hunter returns home with lots of money in his saddlebags only to be robbed at gunpoint by a trio of no-good town citizens, prompting an eventual revenge quest.

Title: 117. The Wrong Box
description: In Victorian England, a fortune now depends on which of two brothers outlives the other, or can be made to have seemed to do so.

Title: 118. The Plague of the Zombies
description: During a mysterious epidemic in a small Cornish village, the local doctor summons his professor friend for help.

Title: 119. The Reptile
description: In a Cornish village, various locals die from mysterious snake bites, but the coroner rules the deaths as heart attacks, until a family of newcomers starts an investigation.

Title: 120. Daleks' Invasion Earth 2150 A.D.
description: Dr. Who and his companions arrive on Earth in the year 2150 AD, only to discover that the planet has been invaded and its population enslaved by the dreaded Daleks.

Title: 121. Massacre Time
description: A prospector and his drunkard brother must fight against the insane and sadistic son of a wealthy rancher, who has dispossessed them of their family farm.

Title: 122. Mademoiselle
description: Residents of a small French town are quick to accuse Manou of arson because he seduced most of the town's women. No one suspects the real culprit, a woman committing random crimes, all in an attempt to draw Manou's attention to herself.

Title: 123. What's Up, Tiger Lily?
description: Woody Allen re-dubs the Japanese spy film Kokusai himitsu keisatsu: Kagi no kagi (1965), turning it into a comedy about an agent pursuing the world's greatest egg salad recipe.

Title: 124. Black Tight Killers
description: A military photographer takes a cute stewardess out to dinner where she is promptly kidnapped. Deciding that he has fallen in love with the girl, our "hero" decides to investigate her kidnapping himself.

Title: 125. The Oscar
description: Arrogant Hollywood actor Frankie Fane is nominated for the Best Actor Academy Award. His friend Hymie Kelly recalls their life together, Frankie's ruthless struggle to the top, and the people Frankie has used and abused to get there.

Title: 126. Lt. Robin Crusoe, U.S.N.
description: A Navy pilot is marooned on an island with a headhunter's daughter and outcast tribal women.

Title: 127. Thunderbirds Are GO
description: When the launch of the first manned mission to Mars goes awry due to sabotage, International Rescue is requested to assist in the mission's second attempt.

Title: 128. Rage
description: A man bitten by a rabid dog in the desert must find help before it's too late.

Title: 129. The Bed and How to Make It!
description: Expelled from school and thrown out of her house, Ellen starts working as a maid in a hotel that belongs to her Aunt Connie.

Title: 130. Triple Cross
description: During WW2, convicted bank robber Eddie Chapman becomes a triple agent working for both the British and the Germans.

Title: 131. Come Drink with Me
description: Bandits kidnap a governor's son and demand their imprisoned leader to be set free in exchange. The governor's daughter, a skilled martial artist, is sent to rescue him, but eventually finds herself overmatched and in need of assistance.

Title: 132. The Fighting Prince of Donegal
description: After inheriting his father's title, the young noble, Hugh O'Connell, is taken hostage by the English viceroy but escapes to lead an uprising.

Title: 133. She Beast
description: A newlywed English tourist and an eccentric Transylvanian Count must work together when the former's beautiful wife is made the bodily host of a horrific witch.

Title: 134. After the Fox
description: An Italian criminal mastermind, impersonating a film director, plans to grab the loot on a beach where a bogus movie is being filmed.

Title: 135. The Quiller Memorandum
description: In the West Berlin of the 1960s, two British agents are killed by a Nazi group, prompting British Intelligence to dispatch agent Quiller to investigate.

Title: 136. A Man Called Adam
description: A famous jazz trumpeter finds himself unable to cope with the problems of everyday life.

Title: 137. The Hero
description: En route to Delhi to receive an award, a Bengali film star reevaluates his success through his fellow passengers, dreams, and past experiences.

Title: 138. The Ghost in the Invisible Bikini
description: A corpse has 24 hours to mastermind a good deed without leaving his crypt, to go "up there" and have his youth restored.

Title: 139. Star Pilot
description: A spaceship from Hydra crashes on Sardinia. Aliens take a scientist, his daughter, technicians and spies hostage to fix their ship. After repairs, aliens abduct the humans but they rebel, sending the ship into deep space.

Title: 140. Gypsy Girl
description: A young, lonely, emotionally challenged teenage girl finds solace in burying dead animals after the sudden traumatic death of a childhood friend ten years earlier.

Title: 141. Dr. Goldfoot and the Girl Bombs
description: Disgraced SIC agent Bill Dexter teams up with bumbling doormen Franco and Ciccio to stop Dr. Goldfoot from using his bikini-clad robot girls to blow up high-ranking NATO generals.

Title: 142. The Red Angel
description: During the Sino-Japanese War, a young army nurse gives sympathy to her patients and falls in love with an impotent doctor who's addicted to morphine.

Title: 143. An Angel for Satan
description: At the end of the 19th century, in a little Italian village by a lake, an old statue is recovered. Soon a series of crimes start and the superstitious people of the village believe that the statue carries an ancient malediction .

Title: 144. The Navy vs. the Night Monsters
description: Beware of the Night Crawlers ... their clutches will disintegrate you!

Title: 145. The Diabolical Dr. Z
description: Woman seeks to avenge her father's death by using a local dancer, with long poisonous fingernails, to do her bidding.

Title: 146. Lost Command
description: French Army colonel Raspeguy leads his paratroopers in battle against the Communist Viet Minh in Indochina and against Algerian guerrillas during the Algerian War.

Title: 147. The Round-Up
description: In Hungary, the national movement led by Kossuth has been crushed and the Austrian hegemony re-established, but partisans carry on with violent actions. In order to root out the guerilla, the army rounds up suspects and jails them in an isolated fort. The authorities do not have the identity of the guerilla leaders, who are supposed to be present among the prisoners. However, they know enough about some of the suspects to apply perfidious forms of coercion effectively.

Title: 148. Africa: Blood and Guts
description: The cruel acts of animal poaching and violence, executions, and tribal slaughtering, all taking place on the African continent.

Title: 149. The Bubble
description: Pregnant woman and husband's plane lands in strange town due to atmospheric disturbance. Townspeople act zombie-like, repeating same actions. Couple trapped, seeking escape as they unravel the mystery behind the eerie phenomenon.

Title: 150. Ebirah, Horror of the Deep
description: Four men searching for one's brother are shipwrecked on Letchi Island, where a terrorist organization developing nuclear weapons have enslaved the natives of Infant Island and command monstrous crustacean named Ebirah.

Title: 151. The Game Is Over
description: In Paris, Maxime visits his wealthy industrialist father Alexandre and his beautiful young Canadian wife, Renée. Alexandre fathered him years ago in a prior marriage and he has come to stay with them after studying in England. Renée tells Maxime that she married Alexandre when she was pregnant following an unhappy love affair; the child was stillborn and the passion between the two has faded. They begin an affair and fall in love with each other. Renée, who came from a wealthy family, asks Alexandre for a divorce. He agrees, on the condition that she leaves the fortune she brought to their marriage invested in his business. Renée accepts this and goes to Switzerland for a divorce. But while she is away, Alexandre confronts his son with two alternatives: he can either run off with now penniless Renée or become engaged to Anne, the daughter of a wealthy banker whose support Alexandre needs for his business. Maxime agrees on the second course of action. Renée returns from Switzerland to find Alexandre holding a ball celebrating Maxime's engagement to Anne. Renée throws herself into the pool to kill herself - but then changes her mind and dripping wet enters the party. Alexandre escorts her to the gymnasium, where she sits and stares into an empty future.

Title: 152. My Sister, My Love
description: Jacob returns home to Sweden after four years in Paris. Charlotte, his sister, plans to marry Baron Alsmeden, which arouses Jacob's jealousy. He flirts with Ebba to take revenge on his sister. Old suppressed feelings awaken between them.

Title: 153. Alvarez Kelly
description: During the Civil War, Mexican cattleman Alvarez Kelly supplies the Union with cattle until Confederate Colonel Tom Rossiter's hungry men force Kelly to change his customers.

Title: 154. Texas Across the River
description: In 1845 Texas, a Louisiana belle is courted by a wanted Spanish nobleman and a Texas brawling gunrunner but her suitors' passionate duel is interrupted by the cavalry and a Comanche attack.

Title: 155. Hunger
description: In 1890, Pontus, the starving writer, wanders the streets of Christiania in search of love and a chance to get his work published. All he meets is defeat and suffering while his sense of reality is withering. One moment he is delighted and the next he curses everybody. Nevertheless, all the time he manages to maintain human dignity and pride.

Title: 156. Destination Inner Space
description: A group of scientists working in a deep-sea research station discovers a strange craft of extraterrestrial origin.

Title: 157. Agent for H.A.R.M.
description: Secret agent tries to stop a scientist who has devised a bacterium that devours the body from within.

Title: 158. The Black Klansman
description: After a black man's daughter is killed by the KKK, he seeks revenge by becoming a Klansman.

Title: 159. Pharaoh
description: Young Pharaoh Ramses XIII clashes with Egypt's clergy over influence on the affairs of the state and its coffers.

Title: 160. The Man Called Flintstone
description: While preparing for a camping trip, Fred Flintstone is enlisted by the Bedrock Secret Service to capture a criminal mastermind after a spy who looks like him is injured on the job.

Title: 161. Teesri Manzil
description: A woman blames a nightclub drummer for the suspicious death of her sister, and seeks revenge. However, the pair work together to solve the mystery and become romantically involved, after he introduces himself under another name.

Title: 162. Huling-Huli ni kumpare si kumare
description: Bobby and Eddie are back again in the funniest sex game.

Title: 163. Beau Geste
description: In 1906, two American brothers join the French Foreign Legion and, led by a sadistic Sergeant-Major, they defend a fort against Berber and Tuareg attack.

Title: 164. Around the World Under the Sea
description: The crew of a five-man submarine travels the world oceans, planting sensors on the ocean floor to warn scientists of any impending earthquakes.

Title: 165. Way... Way Out
description: In a futuristic world, the USA decides to send a married couple of astronauts to its moon base in order to prevent any improper contact with the Soviet female cosmonauts manning the USSR moon base.

Title: 166. The Singing Nun
description: Fanciful biography of the Belgian nun who briefly made the hit parade.

Title: 167. Kiss the Girls and Make Them Die
description: In this spoof of spy films, CIA agent, Kelly, is in Rio De Janeiro spying on a wealthy industrialist, David Ardonian, who secretly plans to turn the world sterile and repopulate it with his harem. UK spy, Susan Fleming, helps Kelly.

Title: 168. What's Cooking in Paris
description: Top-notch french restaurant owner Monsieur Septime is involved into crime when one of his famous guests disappears.

Title: 169. The Wild World of Batwoman
description: Batwoman and her bevy of Batmaidens fight evil and dance.

Title: 170. The Hot Month of August
description: A chance encounter with an international playboy and a clandestine affair with a cryptic married woman entangle an unsuspecting young man in a well-planned conspiracy. Has anyone emerged unscathed from the unbreakable shackles of passion?

Title: 171. The Dacians
description: The Dacian kingdom lies at the eastern border of the Roman Empire.Only the river Danube separates the two mortal enemies.The Dacian king Decebalus knows that soon the vastly superior Roman legions will cross the river and attack Dacia.

Title: 172. Chamber of Horrors
description: A one-handed madman uses various detachable devices as murder weapons to gain revenge on those he believes have wronged him.

Title: 173. Chafed Elbows
description: A welfare recipient marries his mother.

Title: 174. The Defector
description: An American scientist is sent by the CIA to East Germany to retrieve a secret microfilm from a Soviet scientist interested in defecting to the West but the Stasi secret police's surveillance complicates matters.

Title: 175. The Creatures
description: A young mute woman, living in a small village, is expecting a baby. Her husband is at the same time writing a novel and using the villagers as his characters. In the creative process, reality and imagination are constantly intertwined.

Title: 176. The Hills Run Red
description: At the end of the Civil War, 2 Confederates holding stolen Union money and chased by Union troops separate, one escaping with the loot and the other getting a 5-year prison term.

Title: 177. Red Roses of Passion
description: Jaded Carla drugs her stuck up aunt and her daughter with mind-altering aphrodisiac concocted from a rose by an ominous Pan sex cult. The women become crazed nymphos and the only way to cure them is for Carla to give herself to "Pan".

Title: 178. Young Törless
description: In a boarding school, a student observes in passive disgust as his two friends manipulate, humiliate and torture a fellow student, justifying their every act.

Title: 179. Venom
description: An amoral young man is invited to the ordinary family house where he seduces the daughter and tries to seduce the mother but is thrashed and thrown out.

Title: 180. Jesse James Meets Frankenstein's Daughter
description: Dr. Maria Frankenstein transplants an artificial brain of her own creation into the skull of Jesse James' slow-witted friend Hank Tracy and names him Igor.

Title: 181. Tarzan and the Valley of Gold
description: Tarzan battles a megalomaniac millionaire named Vinero, who kidnaps a young boy whom he believes can lead him to a legendary city of gold. Vinero is accompanied by his own army, including henchman Mr. Train and gorgeous Sophia.

Title: 182. Assault on a Queen
description: A motley crew of treasure hunters plan to rob the cruise-liner RMS Queen Mary, using a recovered WW2 German submarine.

Title: 183. Kaleidoscope
description: Romantic comedy which has Barney Lincoln and Angel McGinnis as a pair of amorous adventurers in the gambling places of London and the Riviera. Barney Lincoln is a rambling gambling man who scores sensational wins at poker and chemin de fer because he has succeeded in marking the original plates for the backs of all the playing cards manufactured in a plant in Geneva and used in all the gambling joints in Europe. In his gambling depredation, Barney is spotted by Angel McGinnis, the daughter of a Scotland Yard Inspector 'Manny' McGinnis on the lookout for a man to do a job. The inspector enlists Barney's help in playing poker with a shady London character whom Scotland Yard wants to force to financial ruin.

Title: 184. The Murder Clinic
description: Patients and staff of an isolated mental hospital are being killed off by a hooded maniac who stalks the halls.

Title: 185. Picture Mommy Dead
description: After her mother's fiery death, Susan leaves an asylum to live with her father and gold-digging stepmother, who schemes with her lover to find the dead woman's missing diamonds through the traumatized girl.

Title: 186. The Hired Killer
description: Clint Harris, a hit-man, is tasked with killing an ex-employee who has become a snitch for the police. After his brothers assassinate him, he is assigned an assistant and faces a tense situation.

Title: 187. The Third Eye
description: A young count living with his domineering mother spirals into madness after his mother and fiancée are killed by his jealous, lovesick servant.

Title: 188. Yngsjömordet
description: In 1889 Sweden, young Per Nilsson has a very domineering mother, Anna Månsdotter. His father died many years ago. Per and his mother have for a long time had an incestuous relationship. But Per marries Hanna for the sake of her money. Per's mother is evilly mean to her, and Per refuses to have sex with her. She starts to suspect that something is going on between her husband and her mother-in-law.

Title: 189. The Brides of Fu Manchu
description: Fu Manchu blackmails several industrialists and scientists into helping him construct a super-weapon by kidnapping their daughters and wives.

Title: 190. The Wild, Wild Planet
description: A deranged scientist is using his employer's top-secret bio-laboratory to engage in clandestine experiments. When he starts kidnapping leading citizens for use in his twisted tests, it's up to rogue cop Mike Halstead to come to the rescue.

Title: 191. The Undertaker and His Pals
description: An undertaker and his two friends, who are restaurateurs, make business by going out on town and killing people; the restaurateurs use body parts for their menu, the entrepreneur buries the rest.

Title: 192. Gunpoint
description: A young, determined sheriff and his posse chase a gang of murderous train robbers, and a kidnapped woman into New Mexico.

Title: 193. Psycho-Circus
description: A circus becomes the location for stolen loot and murder.

Title: 194. Morgan!
description: After his wife leaves him for his former best friend, a failed London artist begins his descent into madness in trying to win her back.

Title: 195. They're a Weird Mob
description: An Italian sports journalist arrives in Australia but finds no work. The only employment he can find is as a builder's labourer. At first, he cannot comprehend the culture, but eventually he finds mateship and romance.

Title: 196. A Man Could Get Killed
description: In Lisbon, an American businessman is mistaken for a British agent with hilarious consequences.

Title: 197. Rantevou ston aera
description: A hopeful Miss Europe 1966 and her girlfriends fall for an aircraftman and his friends. To be together, they take advantage of their commander's adoration for the famous actress, Rena Vlahopoulou. Who says no to a rendezvous with love?

Title: 198. Missione speciale Lady Chaplin
description: Lady Chaplin is a beautiful woman, she is a fashion stylist and she owns an atelier in Paris. Zoltan is a rich American specialized in submarine researches. Dick Malloy is an American secret agent. What have the three in common? Perhaps a sunk American atomic submarine with sixteen missiles still on board? And why every other scene one, two, ten or more men are trying to kill Malloy in every conceivable way?

Title: 199. Trans-Europ-Express
description: A director, producer and assistant take the Trans-Europ-Express from Paris to Antwerp, where they brainstorm ideas for a film about a greenhorn drug smuggler and a kinky prostitute.

Title: 200. Here Is Your Life
description: A working class teenager comes of age in 1910s rural Sweden, moving from job to job and meeting a variety of individuals who gradually shape his future.

Title: 201. The Birds, the Bees and the Italians
description: Three stories, all set in Treviso. Various couple experience adultery at a party, a bank clerk abandons his wife for his mistress and all the men in the end are prosecuted for having intercourse with an underage girl.

Title: 202. Let's Kill Uncle
description: A 12-year-old orphan who has just inherited a fortune is trapped on an island with his uncle, a former British Intelligence commander who intends to kill him. A young girl is the boy's only ally against the sarcastic uncle, who uses hypnotism, a pool of sharks, fire, and poisonous mushrooms as weapons.

Title: 203. Lord Love a Duck
description: A bright satirical comedy about an innocent high school girl granted her wishes by a student prodigy. A broad satire of teenage culture in the sixties, its targets ranging from progressive education to beach movies.

Title: 204. Amrapali
description: A victory over neighboring state Vaishai has always eluded Magadh Samrat Ajaatshatru despite being winning and taking control over all neighboring states. He attacks Vaishali only get defeated again. Wounded, lost and on the run, Ajaatshatru dons the guise of a Vaishali soldier and takes shelter with a woman named Amrapali and they fall in love with each other. Ajaatshatru finds an ally in Senapati Balbadhra Singh and both start a plot to gain control of Vaishali. Vaishali Samrat comes to know about Ajaatshatru and Amrapali's liaison with him, he sentences her with a death penalty. Ajaatshatru is enraged at this, he gathers together his armies and storms the unsuspecting Vaishali and virtually burns the city down, killing almost everyone in it. This accomplished, he rushes to free his beloved from the dungeons. He does set her free but it is not the same Amrapali; this Amrapali is quite different. She is not at all thrilled to be in the presence of her conqueror lover. She teaches him what he won in the battle ground but what he lost in reality.

Title: 205. Who Killed the Cat?
description: A scheming widow tries to persecute three old ladies, but fate takes its revenge on her.

Title: 206. Blindfold
description: A New York psychiatrist is solicited by government agents in connection with a former patient of his who also happens to be a scientist wanted by certain foreign powers.

Title: 207. Mondo Keyhole
description: Howard Thorne is a rapist in Los Angeles: he meets women at work and at parties or he sees them walking down the street, and he follows them, terrifies them, and assaults them. He also dreams about these assaults, and he's unclear how much of what he's done is real and how much is fantasy. He ignores his heroin-using wife, Vicki, who tries everything she can think of to get his sexual attention. Howard and Vicki go separately to a costume party where she learns the full truth about his nature and where he is stalked by one of his recent victims. Individualized versions of Hell await Howard and Vicki.

Title: 208. $1,000 on the Black
description: Twelve years ago, Sartana framed his brother Johnny for murder and stole his girlfriend. Now the town's undisputed boss and doted over by his possessive mother, Sartana seems safe - until, his sentence served, Johnny rides back into town.

Title: 209. Once Before I Die
description: WW-II 1941: Shortly after Pearl Harbor the Japanese attack the Philippine islands. A group of Polo playing soldiers and their families are surprised far off in the countryside. Lt. Bailey leads them back to Manila, but the streets are jammed with fugitives. On the trip Bailey's fiancée Alex talks with a 22 years old shy soldier. He tells her of his fears to die and admits that he's never been with a woman. Only once before he dies, he'd like to have sex.

Title: 210. Man from Nowhere
description: After getting sprung from prison by a Mexican bandit, a bounty hunter is hired to protect a town by the father of a saloon girl killed by a member of the bandit's gang.

Title: 211. The Tall Women
description: Seven women are the only survivors of an Apache attack on a wagon train. They must cross the desert on foot to escape the Indians who are hunting them.

Title: 212. L'armata Brancaleone
description: A group of misfits, headed by an incompetent knight named Brancaleone, set out to reach the small town of Aurocastro so that their leader can take possession of the fief.

Title: 213. Secret Agent Super Dragon
description: A series of murders in Michigan lead an American secret agent to Amsterdam, where he uncovers a plot to imperil the world with a potent new drug.

Title: 214. The Queens
description: Four unrelated short comedies by four different directors. "Queen Sabina" chronicles the sexual misadventures of a teenage girl on the road home. "Queen Armenia" centers on a self-serving opportunistic gypsy babysitter who uses her employer's kids for her own gain. "Queen Elena" centers on a husband who learns a lesson about the perils of infidelity after he succumbs to the wiles of the seductive wife next door. "Queen Marta" centers on a wealthy woman who, when drunk, uses her butler as an outlet for her lust.

Title: 215. Daimajin
description: A giant stone statue comes to life to protect the residents of a small town against the depradations of an evil warlord.

Title: 216. The Pornographers
description: While avoiding the mob and local authorities, a world-weary pornographer finds being a family man the most difficult as he wrestles with his own desires and afflictions.

Title: 217. Ambush Bay
description: A Marine unit on a Japanese-held island in the Philippines tries to hook up with local Filipino guerrillas.

Title: 218. Atout coeur à Tokyo pour OSS 117
description: After an American Navy base is annihilated by a secret weapon, Agent OSS 117 is sent to Japan to investigate the organization that's claiming responsibility, and threatening the US with another attack, if they don't pay.

Title: 219. The Witches
description: Following a horrifying experience with the occult in Africa, a schoolteacher moves to a small English village, only to discover that black magic resides there as well.

Title: 220. The Great St. Trinian's Train Robbery
description: The all-girl school foil an attempt by train robbers to recover two and a half million pounds hidden in their school.

Title: 221. Death Curse of Tartu
description: A group of student archaeologists venture into the Florida Everglades to look for fossils, but come across an area cursed by a Native American witch doctor.

Title: 222. Terror Beneath the Sea
description: A group of surface dwellers comes upon an underwater city ruled by a mad scientist and his amphibious servants.

Title: 223. Gamera vs. Barugon
description: A giant monster that emits a destructive ray from its back attacks Japan and takes on Gamera.

Title: 224. The Fat Spy
description: Off the coast of Florida, a nearly-deserted island is rumored to have the fountain of youth. A boatload of teenage kids are headed there for a scavenger hunt.

Title: 225. A Smell of Honey, a Swallow of Brine
description: A young woman teases, seduces, and emotionally destroys young men for her own twisted enjoyment.

Title: 226. Come imparai ad amare le donne
description: Robert chases out into the world to unravel the mystery of women.

Title: 227. The Deadly Bees
description: Trouble strikes when an exhausted pop singer, sent on a vacation to a farm, realizes that the farm's owner raises deadly bees.

Title: 228. Secrets of a Windmill Girl
description: Exploitation film about the tragic life of a Windmill girl called Pat Lord, a fictional dancer in London's real-life historical striptease nightclub and nudie film theater, the (in)famous Windmill Theatre.

Title: 229. The Psychopath
description: Four men who were involved in the investigation of a German millionaire at the end of World War II are found murdered with tiny dolls left next to their corpses.

Title: 230. Moonlighting Wives
description: Tired of being in debt, an ambitious housewife sets up a stenography business. Finding that her clients are more interested in the women than the dictation, she turns it into a profitable prostitution ring made up of neighbourhood wives.

Title: 231. Rat Pfink and Boo Boo
description: After stopping three crooks from robbing an innocent woman, two dimwits become crime fighters.

Title: 232. Die Nibelungen, Teil 1 - Siegfried
description: Volker von Alzey, the royal bard of the Burgunds (far greater then modern Burgundy), ruled by the Christian, papist king Gunther, who has two brave, loyal brothers and a sister Kriemhild, tells in rhyme the tale of Siegfried of Xanthen, who in the northern kingdom of the Lowlands was a forgery apprentice, till his jealous rival's attack made him drench his blade in blood, which made it all-splitting, the right means to slay the feared-most dragon, Rachnir, whose blood makes him, once bathed in it, invulnerable; Alberich, king of the Alves, whose helmet of invisibility he beats, shows him the dragon-protected ring of the Nibelungen, and he sets out by ship for Iceland, to awake its maiden queen Brunhild, but refuses to stay with her, returning southward to rule from Xanthen on the Rhine and seek himself a queen. Siegfried challenges Gunther at Easter to a duel for both realms, is however proposed instead a preferable marital alliance with Gunther's sister Kriemhild. Just after their betrothal invades Ludegast, king of the Saxons, who however swears allegiance to Burgundy when defeated but spared in duel by Siegfried. Now Gunther demands, for Kriemhild's hand, Siegfried gets him Brunhild as politically ideal bride for Burgundy. Siegfried manages this, but only by using more magic, which will later come at a terrible price...

Title: 233. The Daydreamer
description: An anthology of fairytales by Hans Christian Andersen: "The Little Mermaid", "The Emperor's New Clothes", "Thumbelina", and "The Garden of Paradise".

Title: 234. Sting of Death
description: A deformed man working for a marine biologist takes revenge on the people that mock him by experimenting with a deadly jellyfish.

Title: 235. Three on a Couch
description: An artist has an opportunity to go to Paris and wants to bring his fiancee along. However, she's a psychiatrist who currently has three female patients who don't like men. So, he guises himself as three different men to gauge their trust and hopefully cure them so that his fiancee can go with him.

Title: 236. Il grande colpo dei 7 uomini d'oro
description: The Professor (Leroy) and his men are captured by U.S. agents during an attempted train robbery. To avoid jail, they must kidnap a Latin dictator. The film is filled with cool sci-fi gadgets, including flying jetpacks. Austin Powers would love this fast moving, groovy sci-fi intrigue thriller. Podesta is a wow! From nice color 16mm print.

Title: 237. Watch Out for the Automobile
description: A very good cop tries to catch a very bad and extremely clever car thief. The irony's that the thief isn't very clever, nor is he a bad person. In fact, he's not just a virtuous person he's also the 'cop's best friend.

Title: 238. War Between the Planets
description: Scientists try to prevent a collision between Earth and a planet that is heading for it.

Title: 239. Judith
description: A beautiful woman who survived a concentration camp goes to Israel in 1948 to track down her Nazi husband who had betrayed her.

Title: 240. Angelique and the King
description: In the third of the Angélique series, the heroine is sent on a mission by King Louis XIV, and later finds herself the subject of rumors.

Title: 241. The War Is Over
description: A veteran Republican fighter's ardent dedication to overthrow of Franco's regime is challenged. He realizes that the center of political struggle has shifted away from him, and is forced to make choices about his life and political ideals.

Title: 242. Billy the Kid Versus Dracula
description: Dracula travels to the American Old West, intent on making a young and beautiful female ranch owner his vampire bride. Her fiance, the reformed outlaw Billy the Kid, finds out about it and rushes to save her.

Title: 243. Texas, Adios
description: A Texan sheriff and his younger brother travel across the border into Mexico to confront the man who killed their father.

Title: 244. Who Wants to Kill Jessie?
description: "What if someone had an absurd dream and the visions ran out in the street?" a scientist asks Rose, a researcher who discovers a way to engender beneficial dreams (to produce contented, productive workers). There's a problem: after an injection of her elixir, dream elements become real. Rose learns this after dosing her husband Henry to stop his dreaming about Jessie, a curvaceous comic-book heroine who has anti-gravitational gloves he needs to study so he can solve a problem at the factory where he's chief engineer: Henry wakes up with Jessie asleep next to him pursued by a cowboy and a super hero. Jealousy consumes Rose. All this plus satire aimed at the Czechoslovak state.

Title: 245. Invasion
description: An alien spaceship crashes near a rural hospital. When the alien is taken to the hospital, a mysterious force field suddenly appears around it.

Title: 246. Gammera the Invincible
description: An atomic explosion awakens Gammera--a giant, fire-breathing turtle monster--from his millions of years of hibernation. Enraged at being roused from such a sound sleep, he takes it out on Tokyo.

Title: 247. My Brother's Wife
description: A man's wife starts having an affair with her brother-in-law, who is temporarily staying at their apartment.

Title: 248. Stop the World: I Want to Get Off
description: The show, set against a circus backdrop, focuses on Littlechap from the moment of his birth until his death. Each time something unsatisfactory happens, he calls out 'Stop the world!' and addresses the audience.

Title: 249. Mera Saaya
description: A lawyer's wife dies in his arms. Yet, another woman - identical in appearance and accused of aiding a gang of bandits - claims to be the lawyer's wife. A courtroom drama ensues.

Title: 250. The Spy with a Cold Nose
description: A dog with a spying device under its skin is sent to the Russian government as a present. When the Russians send the dog to a veterinary, British spy must get to the dog first and retrieve the spying device.

Title: 251. Boy, Did I Get a Wrong Number!
description: A seductive starlet flees Hollywood and causes chaos for a real estate agent.

Title: 252. Not with My Wife, You Don't!
description: During the Korean War, an Italian nurse falls for two American pilots. She marries one, believing the other died. Years later, the presumed-dead pilot resurfaces, complicating her marriage.

Title: 253. Girl on a Chain Gang
description: Three young people are framed, arrested, and thrown into prison by corrupt Southern police.

Title: 254. Violence at Noon
description: Two young women must come to terms with the fact that a man they're deeply linked to is a murdering rapist.

Title: 255. L'enfer sur la plage
description: Alex, a former mercenary out of business, lives on a yacht anchored off Antibes with his wife, the beautiful and tight Helen and John, her former lover.

Title: 256. Mister Buddwing
description: An amnesiac (James Garner) wanders the streets of Manhattan trying to figure out who he is.

Title: 257. Wings
description: A fascinating and human portrayal of a once-famous fighter pilot and loyal Stalinist named Nadezhda Petrovna. Now a 41-year-old provincial schoolmistress, she has so internalized the military ideas of service and obedience that she cannot adjust to life in peacetime.

Title: 258. The Girls on F Street
description: A man visits a club and faces consequences when his wife discovers his actions. A sculptor and model struggle with their feelings. Another man's visit to a club leads to a dramatic confrontation.

Title: 259. Teesri Kasam
description: A naive bullock-cart driver falls for a traveling courtesan.

Title: 260. One of Our Spies Is Missing
description: U.N.C.L.E. agents Napoleon Solo and Illya Kuryakin are sent to Europe where a scientist's age-reversing machine is in danger of being seized by T.H.R.U.S.H. spies.

Title: 261. Dutchman
description: With the provocation of her lovely half-naked body and strikingly lascivious speech, Lula, a sinister, neurotic white girl, lures to his doom Clay, a good-looking young Black stranger whom she has picked up in the subway and starts mocking for wearing the clothes and employing the voice and manners of the conventional white intellectual. At first Clay sees no reason to resist Lula's advances; only when it's too late does he realise she's using him, drops his "'white' disguise" and launches a wild, bitter counterattack on her and on the entire white race.

Title: 262. Line of Demarcation
description: 1941. A little town in the Jura is cut in half by a river that forms the border between German-occupied France and the free zone.

Title: 263. The War of the Planets
description: In the 21st century, aliens invade the solar system.

Title: 264. That Riviera Touch
description: Two friends decide to have a holiday in the south of France. Arriving at a deserted villa, they soon become involved with a gang of jewel thieves and a beautiful woman.

Title: 265. Kid Rodelo
description: An embittered ex-convict cowboy sets out to find the hidden gold his partner told him about.

Title: 266. Hip Hot and 21
description: Naïve young country gal Diane gets sold by her abusive father to hunky stud Rick for only fifty bucks. Alas, Rick turns out to be a total no-account jerk who leaves Diane high and dry to fend for herself in a cheap apartment after spending a single night with her. Pretty soon Diane finds herself in all kinds of trouble with the low-life characters who live in the apartment with her.

Title: 267. Moment to Moment
description: A psychiatrist's wife thinks her French Riviera lover is dead.

Title: 268. Any Wednesday
description: Ellen Gordon, a New York executive's mistress, falls for the executive's young business associate when he is accidentally sent to use the apartment where the executive and Ellen meet every Wednesday.

Title: 269. Wake Up and Die
description: Luciano Lutring is a dangerous fugitive in Italy, he meets Candida, a nightclub singer and they fall in love. On their back is Candida's lover Franco Magni, a two-bit gangster. Powered by his new-found fame and reputation, Lutring increasingly becomes more and more reckless, robbing as many jewelry stores as he can and pawning them before the cops catch up with him. One of the first of many poliziesco movies of the time and based on the life of real-life criminal Luciano Lutring; the infamous jewelry thief also known as the "machine gun soloist", a name he acquired by the media by keeping his weapon in a violin case.

Title: 270. Ringo and His Golden Pistol
description: A Mexican bandit teams up with a band of renegade Native Americans to avenge his older brothers when they are killed by a prankster, gold-obsessed bounty hunter.

Title: 271. Oh, Beautiful Istanbul
description: Black comedy about a girl who runs away from her rural village to Istanbul to become and actress and an old drunkard street photographer.

Title: 272. Phool Aur Patthar
description: A criminal young man decides to reform himself for a left away widowed woman. But their relationship faces challenges.

Title: 273. 10:30 P.M. Summer
description: A group of tourists, which relations are already complicated enough, faces with local crime incident.

Title: 274. Arrivederci, Baby!
description: Nick tries to kill his wife to get her money, but when learning of this, she plans the same for him!

Title: 275. Sound of Horror
description: When a group of isolated people in the Greek mountains set off a cave explosion, they are menaced by an invisible shrieking dinosaur that had been buried for eons.

Title: 276. Irezumi
description: A seductive woman gets kidnapped into prostitution. After getting a spider tattoo made on her back, she grows vengeful, leaving several men in her path.

Title: 277. Cartes sur table
description: A mad scientist uses his army of mechanical monsters to control people who have Type O blood.

Title: 278. Kimba, the White Lion
description: The story of a white lion cub growing to become the king of the jungle. The movie is an edited version of the 1965 Japanese television series of the same name based on the eponymous 1950s manga.

Title: 279. Gogola
description: A scientist must find a way to destroy a giant, prehistoric beast that has been ravaging the city.

Title: 280. Suraj
description: Maharaja Vikram decides to marry his daughter Anuradha to his commander's son, Pratap. However, years later, Anuradha is abducted by bandit Suraj while on her way to Pratap's coronation.

Title: 281. Left-Handed Fate
description: The inhabitants of a strange desert Barcelona are gradually leaving the city in a panic group. The victims of a serial killers seem to feel strangely attracted by their executioners. Only Gim, an attractive blonde advertising model, decides to face her destiny.

Title: 282. The Ugly Ones
description: An escapee Mexican outlaw returns to his hometown, where he is sheltered from a tenacious bounty killer by the townspeople - who discover too late that he is a changed man.

Title: 283. An Eye for an Eye
description: A former bounty hunter teams up with a younger one, to track down and kill the wanted gang leader who murdered his wife and little boy.

Title: 284. One Spy Too Many
description: U.N.C.L.E. agents Solo and Kuryakin try to stop a megalomaniac who thinks he's like Alexander The Great, commits offenses against the ten commandments and steals chemical weapons from the army in order to achieve world domination.

Title: 285. Man on the Spying Trapeze
description: An American spy travels to Beirut where he's attacked by agents seeking a valuable microfilm.

Title: 286. Let's Not Get Angry
description: Antoine helps two former acquaintances escape the country, who repay him with a debt transfer. All he has to do is collect from some Léonard Michalon, but for that he will have to go into much trouble to keep the man alive.

Title: 287. Kutsukake Tokijiro - yukyo ippiki
description: According to the code of the gamblers, Tokijiro, though he dislikes killing, has to join in the fighting when afforded a night's stay and meals at the home of a town boss. He will be tested again and again in the bloody tale.

Title: 288. Fiebre de juventud
description: Carlos and Luis drop out of school and try to make it big with a music group, with considerable success. They travel to Ecuador and they meet the beautiful Rita and her daughter Silvia.

Title: 289. Kiss Kiss - Bang Bang
description: Kirk Warren, a former spy, is to be executed because he tried to steal a million dollars. But he is saved by Colonel Smithson because Sir Wilcox has prepared a mission for him. Warren has to steal a secret formula in Switzerland and try to expose the real identity of Mr. X. Kirk leaves London and Alina, his girl, together with three clumsy friends to accomplish his not so secret mission. But Kirk's great love is always a million dollars and not a secret formula.

Title: 290. Shoot Loud, Louder... I Don't Understand
description: Stuck in a dream world of his own, Italian sculptor Albert Saporito (Marcello Mastroianni) sometimes has difficulty separating truth from fiction. When he dreams that his gangster neighbor has been murdered, he reports the crime to the Police, only to involve himself in a complicated situation.

Title: 291. The Projected Man
description: A scientist experimenting with matter transmission by means of a laser beam decides to use himself as a test specimen. But the process goes awry, and one side of his body becomes deformed and lethal to anyone it touches.

Title: 292. The Black Cat
description: A mentally unbalanced man is obsessed with the idea that a black cat is possessed. He tortures and kills it. Later, he comes to believe that the cat has returned from the dead to kill him.

Title: 293. Santa's Christmas Circus
description: Whizzo the clown takes a bunch of kids on a magic carpet ride to the North Pole to see Santa Claus, but not before the kids (members of the Johnny Miller Dance Studio) perform as circus animals in "Whizzoland."

Title: 294. The Frozen Dead
description: A crazed scientist (Dana Andrews) keeps the heads of Nazi war criminals alive until he can find appropriate bodies on which to attach them so he can revive the Third Reich.

Title: 295. Fireball 500
description: Two race car drivers get caught up in a moonshine operation while competing for titles and women.

Title: 296. A Grande Cidade ou As Aventuras e Desventuras de Luzia e Seus 3 Amigos Chegados de Longe
description: Luzia comes from the backwoods of Northeast Brazil to Rio de Janeiro, in search of her fiancé. But soon she'll find out he has turned into a dangerous criminal and is being looked after by the police.

Title: 297. Take Me Naked
description: A troubled homeless man develops an unhealthy fixation on a comely young woman likes to walk around her apartment in the nude.

Title: 298. Adulterio all'italiana
description: To get her husband more interested in her, the wife invents a lover. The husband will collect every hint trying to figure out who is the lover.

Title: 299. Carriage to Vienna
description: A WW2 story of a young Austrian soldier running from the Russian army and a woman whom he forces to come along in order to save his wounded mate.

Title: 300. Return of the Gunfighter
description: An aging gunman and a wounded drifter come upon a young Mexican girl, and agree to help her avenge the death of her father, who was murdered for their land.

Title: 301. The Texican
description: A former Texas sheriff, living in Mexico, goes to Arizona to investigate the murky circumstances under which his brother, a peaceful newspaperman, was killed.

Title: 302. The Republic of ShKID
description: Gang boys from the streets of St. Petersburg, Russia are being tamed and educated at SHKID - Dostoevsky School.

Title: 303. Kriminal
description: A mastermind thief known as Kriminal narrowly escapes execution. He always manages to stay one step ahead of the law with each new crime he commits. Will Kriminal be able to pull of his biggest score yet or will a double cross lead to his demise?

Title: 304. Red Midnight
description: A Doctor, his wife and their friend help and injured man who is part of a foreign spy ring that plans to set off nuclear bombs throughout the US. The unsuspecting good samaritans are taken hostage after the injured man reveals the plans before dying, fearing the horror of a nuclear holocaust the Doctor convinces the spies to set fires to cities instead knowing it would be possible for the US cities to recover from fires. The Doctor and his friend while appearing to have joined the foreign agents eventually plan to thwart the remaining danger of the nuclear bombs by warning the FBI that one of them will be detonated in the Cape Cod area.

Title: 305. The Hunt
description: Three men go hunting rabbits during a hot day. Heat and talking about events that happened in the past make them angry, until they go totally crazy.

Title: 306. The Christmas That Almost Wasn't
description: Santa has to get a job as Santa to earn money to pay his overdue rent bill

Title: 307. Misunderstood
description: A study of bitter relationships between a widower and his two sons.

Title: 308. Johnny Yuma
description: A conniving wife has her husband murdered, and also plans to kill his nephew, the only heir, with the assistance of her ex-lover. When she tries to double-cross the ex-lover, he and the heir team up and kill her bodyguards.

Title: 309. Killer's Carnival
description: A lady killer tracked by the police, takes refuge at a psychiatrist's home, and the doctor tells him three stories, to convince him that crime does not pay. In Vienna, an investigative reporter is run down by a car when he is researching a gang that produces fake diamonds; his sister calls a friend for help, and the man almost suffers a similar fate. In Rome, an underground agent is tortured and almost loses his life to get some documents, and free a woman agent from a spy ring, only to be told by his superior that the documents he had got were fake. In San Francisco, a private detective prevents a lady killer from dying, like five other barmaids of the Flamingo nightclub; all the girls had known the identity of the man - who was planning to kill Brazil's president during the Carnival in Rio de Janeiro.

Title: 310. The Upper Hand
description: In Paris, a gold smuggler is at war with other local gangsters who want piece of the action. Then the mob shows up and makes things worse. Also, an undercover US Treasury Department agent is trying to infiltrate the smuggler's business.

Title: 311. Samurai Wolf
description: A charismatic ronin gets snared into a conflict between officials at a waystation, and gains the enmity of a group of thugs.

Title: 312. The Incredible Sex Revolution
description: Troubled young lass Margaret 'Peggy' Bardot candidly discusses her sexual hang-ups with a psychologist. Bardot's past negative experiences are related in flashback while the psychologist does his to figure out the root cause of her problems.

Title: 313. By a Man's Face Shall You Know Him
description: Korean gangsters try to take over from their Japanese counterparts in post war Japan.

Title: 314. Six Kids and Their Uncle
description: Child psycologist and bachelor, Eric Lund, has written a thesis about the use of psycology in modern parenting. While house sitting for his sitter, he finds himself at the mercy of his sisters six children as he tries to live by the rules of his own thesis while writing his master in child psycology, keeping the household going and staying out of trouble from the nosy neighbours.

Title: 315. Anupama
description: Mohan Sharma (Tarun Bose) is a workaholic whose life changes dramatically after his wife dies giving birth to their daughter Uma (Sharmila Tagore). He despises the daughter by day, and adores her when drunk at night. Uma's life gets better as she comes of age and has a relationship with a sensitive poet, Ashok (Dharmendra), who slowly brings her out of her shell.

Title: 316. The Treasure of San Gennaro
description: An American gangster in Italy enlists a local gang to help him steal the treasure of Naples' patron saint.

Title: 317. Little Girls
description: Four young teenage girls are betrayed by a supposed "friend" and sold to a perverted nightclub owner who ties them up, whips them and then forces them into prostitution.

Title: 319. The Priest and the Girl
description: In a small town in Minas Gerais, the arrival of a young priest causes a commotion in the conservative atmosphere of the place, aggravated by the sudden attraction this priest feels for a beautiful girl. This forbidden love affair soon turns into an unbridled passion.

Title: 320. Las Vegas Hillbillys
description: A Hillbilly hits the big time in Las Vegas.

Title: 321. Slap af Frede!
description: A Chinese diplomat is kidnapped in Genève and the world peace is at risk. The trail leads to Denmark and the danish secret service brings in their best agent, Smith. To accompany Smith they once again turn to novelty salesman Frede Hansen.

Title: 322. Aroused
description: In Manhattan, prostitutes are being murdered by a psycho. A detective is assigned to track him down and bring him in.

Title: 323. An American Dream
description: A TV talk-show host who may have killed his wife finds himself being pursued by both the police and a gang of hoods.

Title: 324. La mujer perdida
description: Sara, son of fishermen, flees from her village and in Madrid she meets Rafael, who helps with her artistic career, but ends up fleeing to Italy where she meets Miguel, a sculptor she falls in love with.

Title: 325. Winnetou and the Crossbreed
description: On her b-day, settler's daughter Apanatschi receives her father's secret gold mine but greedy neighboring prospectors resort to murder and kidnapping in order to get the gold, forcing the girl and her brother to seek Winnetou's protection.

Title: 326. Maya
description: An American boy runs away in the Indian jungle after a fight with his father.

Title: 327. Who Are You, Polly Maggoo?
description: A model tells a television crew about her dreams of a life with Prince Charming while she is fending off the lecherous advances of a horde of men.

Title: 328. Haiducii
description: During the 18th century in the mountains of Wallachia, a band of outlaws aims to undermine the rule of the Phanariots and the Ottomans. Two stepbrothers, Sarbu and Amza, lead this band with their complex and violent relationship.

Title: 329. Fort Yuma Gold
description: Captured Confederate raider Gary Diamond agrees to work with the Yankees to prevent any further bloodshed by warning a Confederate regiment against attacking heavily defended Yankee Fort Yuma.

Title: 330. Galia
description: Newly arrived in Paris, Galia lives in a small apartment near Notre-Dame cathedral. One evening, whilst walking along the banks of the River Seine, she saves a young woman from drowning.

Title: 331. The Venetian Affair
description: Former CIA man, Bill Fenner, now a downbeat, loner journalist, is sent to Venice to investigate the shock suicide bombing by an American diplomat at a peace conference.

Title: 332. Scusi, lei è favorevole o contrario?
description: Successful 50-year-old entrepreneur Tullio Conforti, opposed to divorce for religious reasons, is in fact separated from his wife and leads a frenetic life divided among numerous lovers.

Title: 333. Waco
description: A lawless town asks the state governor to pardon an imprisoned gunfighter in order to hire him as sheriff but various factions plan to kill the new sheriff and take over the town.

Title: 334. Castle of Evil
description: The relatives of a recently deceased man named Kovac gather at is creepy mansion for the reading of the will. Before the will can be read, however, the relatives began to be murdered one by one.

Title: 335. Spies Strike Silently
description: A young blonde Jane Freeman is found dead in the pool. She turns out to be a daughter of Professor Freeman who has been told his daughter will die unless he gives up his research.

Title: 336. The Sandwich Man
description: A man with a sandwich-board (advert) wanders around London meeting many strange characters.

Title: 337. Orlovi rano lete
description: A group of kids from the Bosnian village often run away from school from the terror of Pepper, a teacher who got his nickname because of his red nose. Soon they formed a brigand division, but have been discovered and caught. The sudden arrival of year 1941 turns their game into reality.

Title: 338. Seven Guns for the MacGregors
description: Gregor and the rest of the MacGregor brothers want to sell horses in Las Mesas where they get into trouble with the locals and evil Santillana. After doing time behind bars and losing their horses they decide to go after Santillana's gang.

Title: 339. Hotel Paradiso
description: Monsieur Feydeau has writer's block, and he needs a new play. But he takes an opportunity to observe the upper class of 1900 Paris, Monsieur Boniface with a domineering wife, and the next-door neglectful husband Henri with a beautiful, but ignored wife, Marcelle. Henri traces architectural anomalies (most ghost sounds are drains), and plans a night at the Hotel Paradiso, but this hotel is the assignation spot of Marcelle and Boniface. One wife, two husbands, a nephew, and the perky Boniface maid, all at this "by the hour" hotel, and consummation of the affair is, to say the least, severely compromised (not the least by a police raid). All of this under Feydeau's eye, and his play is the "success fou" of the next season.

Title: 340. Red Zone Cuba
description: Escaped convict Griffin and his friends ran all the way to Hell...with a penny, and a broken cigarette.

Title: 341. Balearic Caper
description: A scepter is stolen, and it's hunted for by various groups of international robbers and spies, for various reasons - in a parody of 007 movies.

Title: 342. My Name Is Pecos
description: A Mexican pistolero exacts revenge on the man responsible for the murder of his family, who has taken over his hometown in an effort to recover money that was stolen during a recent robbery.

Title: 343. New York City... Melting Point
description: A documentary about New York City produced in collaboration with the United States Information Agency (USIA) for educational and information purposes.

Title: 344. Press for Time
description: The British P.M.'s grandson, Norman, becomes a reporter for a provincial newspaper in Teignmouth where he causes hilarious chaos.

Title: 345. La vida de Pedro Infante
description: A tender story based on the real life of Pedro Infante, actor and singer, an icon of Mexican cinema. His beginnings, his triumphs, his loves and his untimely death.

Title: 346. Django Shoots First
description: Django's father is framed by his business partner Clusker and shot by a bounty Killer. Django inherits his fathers part of the business and a score to settle with Clusker.

Title: 347. Roundabout
description: Every Sunday, lonely bachelor and refined judge Mladen goes to play chess with his friend, sculptor Fedji. Slowly, he engages in a love affair with Neda, Fedia's wife, and almost invisibly, a love triangle forms.
